crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Detects vulnerable driver mentioned in LOLDrivers project using VersionInfo values from the PE header - WinRing0.sys, WinRing0x64
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Florian Roth

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a Windows kernel driver identified as WinRing0 (confirmed by the PDB path and device name '\Device\WinRing0_1_2_0'). It functions as a hardware abstraction layer that exposes dangerous kernel-level primitives to user-mode applications via IOCTLs. These capabilities include: 1) Direct Port I/O (IN/OUT instructions), 2) Reading/Writing Model Specific Registers (MSRs) via __rdmsr/__wrmsr, 3) Accessing PCI configuration space via HalGetBusDataByOffset/HalSetBusDataByOffset, and 4) Mapping arbitrary physical memory into virtual space using MmMapIoSpace (sub_11504). While used by legitimate system utilities, this driver is a frequent target for 'Bring Your Own Vulnerable Driver' (BYOVD) attacks, where malware leverages its signed status to gain arbitrary kernel execution and bypass security protections like Driver Signature Enforcement (DSE).
